"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433933","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-12-09","<p>There is no policy to delay the determination of shale gas planning proposals pending the completion of the Environment Agency’s consultation on their updated Onshore Oil and Gas Sector Guidance issued on 26 November.</p><p>The Government has in place a comprehensive regulatory framework for shale gas development. As part of this, the Environment Agency’s views on schemes can be taken into account by local planning authorities, or by the Secretary of State where relevant, in the determination of planning proposals for shale gas development.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2015-12-09T17:15:23.117Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433933/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433933/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433933/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-12-03","Fracking: Planning Permission","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what his policy is on pausing planning applications to build shale gas wells until after the Environment Agency has completed its consultation and published guidance for onshore oil and gas operations in the UK.","false","Biography information for Mark Menzies","Fylde","Mark Menzies","18624"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433934","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-12-10","<p>A planning appeal is a quasi-judicial process, and every application needs to be considered on its individual merits, with due process, in light of the relevant material considerations. To avoid prejudicing the decisions, I should not comment further but can reassure my hon. Friend that all relevant issues identified by local people in the current appeals by Cuadrilla Resources will be given very careful consideration.</p>","Stockton South","James Wharton",,"2015-12-10T16:26:59.547Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433934/answer","Biography information for James Wharton","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433934/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433934/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-12-03","Fracking: Lancashire","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what he weight he plans to give to the views of people living close to the proposed shale gas well at Roseacre and Preston New Road in the process for considering planning appeals by Cuadrilla Resources to build wells at those sites.","false","Biography information for Mark Menzies","Fylde","Mark Menzies","18625"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433935","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2016-02-16","<p>The number of empty homes is at its lowest since records began. Local authorities have powers and strong incentives to tackle empty homes. Through the New Homes Bonus they earn the same financial reward for bringing an empty home back into use as building a new one. Councils may also charge up to 150% council tax for homes empty for over two years. In addition, we have reformed permitted development rights to free up the planning system and encourage the conversion of existing commercial buildings into residential units</p><p>A local authority can also serve a notice under section 215 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 to make good land and buildings that are not being properly maintained where the public amenity the area is being adversely affected. Where a section 215 notice has not been complied with, the local planning authorities can carry out the works and seek to recover the costs. Additionally local authorities also have powers under sections 76-79 of the Building Act to dealing with defective premises, dangerous buildings, ruinous/dilapidated buildings and neglected sites; section 29 of the Local Government (Miscellaneous Provisions) Act 1982 for works on unoccupied buildings; and sections 79-82 of the Environmental Protection Act for abatement or prohibition of a nuisance.</p><p>Advice to local planning authorities on how to make the best use of their powers under Section 215 of the Town and Country Planning Act 1990 can be found at: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/town-and-country-planning-act-1990-section-215-best-practice-guidance" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/town-and-country-planning-act-1990-section-215-best-practice-guidance</a></p>","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2016-02-16T12:42:06.957Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433935/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433935/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433935/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-12-03","Derelict Land","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, what steps his Department is taking to reduce the number of derelict and abandoned buildings.","false","Biography information for Mike Kane","Wythenshawe and Sale East","Mike Kane","18650"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433936","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-12-09","<p>The Government consulted on issues related to the must offer provision in the Communications Act in its consultation – ‘The balance of payments between television platforms and public service broadcasters’. Analysis of responses is ongoing and the Government will publish a response in due course.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-12-09T09:52:13.837Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433936/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433936/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433936/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-12-03","Digital Broadcasting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, for what reasons DTT platforms were excluded from the scope of his Department's balance of payments consultation.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","18664"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433937","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-12-08","<p>Work is continuing on the detailed policy design of the replacement for the existing levy. We will make a further announcement in due course.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2015-12-08T09:41:44.3Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433937/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433937/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433937/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-12-03","Horse Racing: Betting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what timetable he has set for the implementation of the Horserace Betting Right; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","18655"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433938","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-12-09","<p>The Government's consultation ‘the balance of payments between television platforms and public service broadcasters’ examined how the public service broadcasters' business models for the distribution for television content work. The focus of this consultation was on the commercial arrangements between broadcasters and PSB platforms - not subscription-free DTT platforms.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-12-09T09:54:10.157Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433938/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433938/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433938/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-12-03","Public Service Broadcasting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what assessment he has made of whether the must offer provision of the Communications Act 2003 is sufficient to ensure access to public service broadcast channels on non-discriminatory terms for all TV platforms.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","18665"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433939","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-12-08","<p>Broadband Delivery UK’s Market Test Pilot scheme has been exploring alternative technologies, including wireless, with the aim of better informing how to provide superfast broadband to the hardest to reach premises. The results of these pilots will be published soon.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-12-08T10:54:41.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433939/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433939/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433939/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-12-03","Broadband","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, when the Government plans to publish its final findings from the eight market test pilots under the Exploring superfast coverage beyond 95 per cent programme.","false","Biography information for Chi Onwurah","Newcastle upon Tyne Central","Chi Onwurah","18666"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433940","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-12-14","<p>To inform work to replace the current levy system, we have commissioned an independent economic analysis of the costs and funding of horseracing. This economic analysis work will also examine relevant comparable models.</p>","Chatham and Aylesford","Tracey Crouch",,"2015-12-14T14:24:39.497Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433940/answer","Biography information for Tracey Crouch","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433940/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433940/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-12-03","Horse Racing: Betting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, whether his Department has examined the funding of horseracing in (a) Ireland and (b) France to inform its policy making on the Horse Betting Levy.","false","Biography information for Sir Nicholas Soames","Mid Sussex","Sir Nicholas Soames","18707"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433941","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-12-08","<p>Ofcom’s Connected Nations Infrastructure Report 2015 states that in May 2015, more than four out of five households had access to broadband of at least 24Mbps; and 98% of premises could access speeds of 2Mbps or more (<a href="http://stakeholders.ofcom.org.uk/binaries/research/infrastructure/2015/downloads/connected_nations2015.pdf" target="_blank">http://stakeholders.ofcom.org.uk/binaries/research/infrastructure/2015/downloads/connected_nations2015.pdf</a>).</p><p>Throughout this month, the Government - working with local authorities and the devolved administrations - is rolling out a scheme to provide access to subsidised satellite broadband to all premises with speeds below 2Mbps. This scheme offers immediate assistance to those homes and businesses in the most remote areas with the slowest speeds and is part of our transformation of the UK's digital landscape. In addition, the Prime Minister recently announced the ambition to give people the legal right to request a connection to broadband with speeds of 10 Mbps, no matter where in the country they live.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-12-08T10:58:27.78Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433941/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433941/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433941/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-12-03","Broadband","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what proportion of households have access to broadband of at least 24Mbps; how many households are unable to receive a service of at least 2Mbps; and how many households use satellite broadband.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","18642"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433942","Department for Culture, Media and Sport","false","2015-12-09","<p>TheDepartment no longer has its own website. DCMS content can be accessed via <a href="http://gov.uk/" target="_blank">GOV.UK</a>. On <a href="http://gov.uk/" target="_blank">GOV.UK</a>you can carry out many actions in Welsh that are important to people in their day to day life, such as apply for car tax, register to vote, book driving theory and practical tests, access state pension details online and apply for a Blue Badge.It also gives government departments and other organisations which publish material on <a href="http://gov.uk/" target="_blank">GOV.UK</a> the ability to publish Welsh-language content in line with the requirements of their individual Welsh-speaking users.</p>","Wantage","Mr Edward Vaizey",,"2015-12-09T09:57:09.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433942/answer","Biography information for Mr Edward Vaizey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433942/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433942/answer",,,,,,,,"10","Culture, Media and Sport","Culture, Media and Sport","2015-12-03","Department for Culture, Media and Sport: Welsh Language","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Culture, Media and Sport, what proportion of the forms on his Department's website is available in Welsh.","false","Biography information for Nia Griffith","Llanelli","Nia Griffith","18756"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433943","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-10","<p>France is operating alongside the UK as part of the international Coalition against Daesh. All Coalition air operations are planned in accordance with international law and every precaution is taken to minimise collateral damage and civilian casualties.</p>","Sevenoaks","Michael Fallon",,"2015-12-10T17:05:32.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433943/answer","Biography information for Sir Michael Fallon","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433943/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433943/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-12-03","Islamic State","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assurances he sought from his French counterpart that, in providing British surveillance assistance to the French bombing of identified ISIS operational buildings in Raqqa following the ISIS-inspired terrorist attacks in Paris, the French military avoided any civilians being killed as collateral damage from the bombings.","false","Biography information for Paul Flynn","Newport West","Paul Flynn","18638"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433944","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-10","<p>The Royal Fleet Auxiliary (RFA) started an Apprentice scheme with Ratings in 2015 and so far 50 apprentices have started training.</p><br /><p>The numbers of Officer Cadets the RFA has trained in each year since 2009-10 are as follows:</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td><p>2009-10</p></td><td><p>25</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2010-11</p></td><td><p>25</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011-12</p></td><td><p>25</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012-13</p></td><td><p>25</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013-14</p></td><td><p>25</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>25</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>30 (to date)</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br />","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier",,"2015-12-10T17:29:47.073Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433944/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433944/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433944/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-12-03","Royal Fleet Auxiliary","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many (a) apprentice ratings and (b) officer cadets the Royal Fleet Auxiliary has trained in each year since 2009-10.","false","Biography information for Ian Mearns","Gateshead","Ian Mearns","18706"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433945","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-09","<p>The Ministerial Working Group has not made any policy decisions on the Royal Fleet Auxiliary (RFA). The role of the RFA in providing logistic support to the Royal Navy (RN) is implicit within the support that the RN provides in delivering the National Strategy for Maritime Security.</p><br />","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-12-09T16:19:36.3Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433945/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433945/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433945/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-12-03","Royal Fleet Auxiliary","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, with reference to paragraph 1.17 of the UK National Strategy for Maritime Security, published in May 2014, how many policy decisions in relation to the Royal Fleet Auxiliary have been taken to date by the ministerial working group on maritime security.","false","Biography information for Ian Mearns","Gateshead","Ian Mearns","18692"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433946","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2015-12-10","<p>As Chairman, I write to the members of the Ministerial Working Group on maritime security biannually with operational and policy updates, the most recent of these was on 19 November. The Ministerial Working Group intends to meet in 2016 to discuss the implications of the National Security Strategy and Strategic Defence and Security Review.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2015-12-10T14:20:13.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433946/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433946/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433946/answer",,,,,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2015-12-03","Seas and Oceans: Security","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, with reference to paragraph 1.17 of the UK National Strategy for Maritime Security, published in May 2014, how many meetings there have been of the ministerial working group on maritime security.","false","Biography information for Ian Mearns","Gateshead","Ian Mearns","18694"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433947","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-09","<p>The National Strategy for Maritime Security was published in May 2014 and remains relevant to today's challenges in the maritime domain. However, as we implement the outcomes of the Strategic Defence and Security Review 2015, we will consider whether the strategy should be reviewed.</p>","Portsmouth North","Penny Mordaunt",,"2015-12-09T16:18:50.62Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433947/answer","Biography information for Penny Mordaunt","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433947/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433947/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-12-03","Royal Fleet Auxiliary","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, if he will take steps to update the National Maritime Security Strategy to 2019 to include the Government's policy on the role of the Royal Fleet Auxiliary.","false","Biography information for Ian Mearns","Gateshead","Ian Mearns","18695"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433948","Ministry of Defence","false","2015-12-10","<p>Maintenance costs for Grantown-On-Spey are accounted within the larger RAF Lossiemouth budget and costs could not be broken down and identified.</p><p>More generally, I refer the hon. Member to the answer my hon. Friend the Minister for Defence Personnel and Veterans (Mark Lancaster) gave on 7 December 2015 to Question number 18570. Some costs for some previous years may be available and Ministry of Defence officials are reviewing available data from a variety of sources. The Minister for Defence Personnel and Veterans will write to the hon. Member and place a copy of his letter in the Library of the House.</p>","Canterbury","Mr Julian Brazier",,"2015-12-10T17:29:03.913Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433948/answer","Biography information for Sir Julian Brazier","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433948/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433948/answer",,,,,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2015-12-03","Military Bases: Grantown-on-Spey","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 2 December 2015 to Question 17679, for what reasons the maintenance costs for FDTC Grantown-on-Spey cannot be broken down; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","18648"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433949","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2015-12-08","<p>The Government is committed to enhancing its support for postgraduate study and wants more people to have the opportunity to build on their academic success through access to a higher level qualification.</p><p>The new Postgraduate Loans for Master’s study are intended to be available for eligible students studying in academic year 2016/17.</p><p>The Government announced on 25 November that the new Postgraduate Loan for Master’s study will be available to individuals up to age 60. Further information is available via the following link:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/postgraduate-study-student-loans-and-other-support" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/consultations/postgraduate-study-student-loans-and-other-support</a></p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2015-12-08T15:28:59.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433949/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433949/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433949/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-12-03","Mature Students: Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, whether people over the initial postgraduate loan age cap of 30 will be able to apply and receive a postgraduate loan of up to £10,000 for the 2016-17 academic year.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","18668"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433950","Department for Education","false","2015-12-08","<p>Initial teacher training (ITT) bursaries of varying amounts are available to eligible trainees, depending on the academic year in which they undertake their ITT, the subject in which they are training to teach and their highest relevant academic award. The amounts and eligible subjects change each year based on assessment of need informed by the targets and past performance.</p><br /><p>Scholarships are awarded to those trainees who have gone through an additional selection procedure over and above that of their chosen ITT provider. These were available in 2012/13 in physics, and from 2013/14 in chemistry, computing, maths and physics.</p><br /><p>The table below shows a breakdown of the total number of trainees who have received training bursaries and scholarships (where relevant) over the last full four academic years, 2011/12, 2012/13, 20/13/14 and 2014/15.</p><p><br></p><p>Table 1: Summary of the number of trainees that received training bursaries or scholarships in academic years 2011/12, 2012/13, 2013/14 and 2014/15</p><br /><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Academic year</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Bursary</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Scholarship</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2011/12</p></td><td><p>6348</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p><strong>6,348</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2012/13</p></td><td><p>16759</p></td><td><p>87</p></td><td><p><strong>16,846</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2013/14</p></td><td><p>17434</p></td><td><p>201</p></td><td><p><strong>17,635</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014/15</p></td><td><p>16359</p></td><td><p>422</p></td><td><p><strong>16,781</strong></p></td></tr></tbody></table><p><br></p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2015-12-08T17:28:38.473Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433950/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433950/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433950/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-12-03","Teachers: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many teachers or trainee teachers received each of the scholarship and bursaries for teacher training courses in each subject in each of the last four years.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","18678"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433951","Department for Education","false","2015-12-09","<p>The Department does not hold this information in the form requested. Academies are operated by the legal entity of academy trusts, many of which operate multiple academies across multiple local authorities. As such, it is not possible to give local authority figures.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","18680","2015-12-09T13:38:08.767Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433951/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433951/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433951/answer","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433951/answer/previousversion/34463","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433951/answer/previousversion/34463",,,"60","Education","Education","2015-12-03","Academies: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many academies in each local authority area were in deficit in each year since 2009-10; and what the total deficit was in academies in each such area in each of those years.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","18679"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433952","Department for Education","false","2015-12-09","<p>The Department does not hold this information in the form requested. Academies are operated by the legal entity of academy trusts, many of which operate multiple academies across multiple local authorities. As such, it is not possible to give local authority figures.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","18679","2015-12-09T13:38:08.827Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433952/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433952/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433952/answer","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433952/answer/previousversion/34462","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433952/answer/previousversion/34462",,,"60","Education","Education","2015-12-03","Academies: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many academies were in deficit in each year since 2009-10; and what the total deficit was in academies in each such year.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","18680"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433953","Department for Education","false","2015-12-08","<p>In the academic year 2015 to 2016 there were 5,440 first year undergraduate trainees.</p><br /><p>The 2015 to 2016 Teacher Supply Model sets the target for postgraduate trainees and takes account of the number of undergraduate trainees completing a course in 2016 when meeting future teacher requirements. We allocated places for undergraduate courses using criteria as set out in the published guidance.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","18685","2015-12-08T17:31:10.333Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433953/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433953/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433953/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-12-03","Teachers: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many new entrants there were in undergraduate programmes by subject for Initial Teacher Training for 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","18682"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433954","Department for Education","false","2015-12-08","<p>The requested information is not available.</p><br /><p>The Department for Education published the 2016/17 Teacher Supply Model (TSM) alongside initial teacher training (ITT) place recruitment controls on 14 October 2015. Both the 2015/16 and 2016/17 versions of the TSM are available online at: <a href="http://www.gov.uk/government/publications/teacher-supply-model" target="_blank">www.gov.uk/government/publications/teacher-supply-model</a></p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2015-12-08T17:30:15.37Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433954/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433954/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433954/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-12-03","Teachers: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what the (a) overall target and (b) target for each subject for new entrants to Initial Teacher Training for 2015-16 is, when the same Teacher Supply Model methodology that was applied in 2014-15 is used.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","18683"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433955","Department for Education","false","2015-12-09","<p>There are eight Regional Schools Commissioners. Profiles on each commissioner are published online: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/schools-commissioners-group/about/our-governance" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/schools-commissioners-group/about/our-governance</a>.</p><br /><p>Regional Schools Commissioners have responsibility for a region. The commissioners are: Sir David Carter (South West England); Dominic Herrington (South England and South East London); Martin Post (South Central England and North West London); Dr Tim Coulson (East of England and North East London); Pank Patel (West Midlands); Jennifer Bexon-Smith (East Midlands and the Humber); Victoria Beer (Lancashire and West Yorkshire); and Janet Renou (North of England).</p><br /><p>The number of schools in each region is listed in the table below. This number is the number of free schools, studio schools, University Technical Colleges, academies and local authority maintained schools.</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Region</p></td><td><p>Number of schools</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>South West England</p></td><td><p>2331</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>South England and South East London</p></td><td><p>3297</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>South Central England and North West London</p></td><td><p>2982</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>East of England and North East London</p></td><td><p>2376</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>West Midlands</p></td><td><p>2671</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>East Midlands and the Humber</p></td><td><p>2667</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Lancashire and West Yorkshire</p></td><td><p>3389</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>North of England</p></td><td><p>1816</p></td></tr></tbody></table><br /><p>We do not hold data on the number of schools in each region which have not been visited by the Regional Schools Commissioner. Regional Schools Commissioners are responsible for approving new academies, intervening in underperforming academies and free schools in their area, and matching underperforming maintained schools with a strong academy sponsor.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2015-12-09T16:53:20.537Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433955/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433955/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433955/answer","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433955/answer/previousversion/34464","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433955/answer/previousversion/34464",,,"60","Education","Education","2015-12-03","Regional School Commissioners","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, who the Regional School Commissioners are; how many schools are located in each of the regions for which they are responsible; and how many schools in their area each commissioner has not visited since taking up that role.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","18684"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433956","Department for Education","false","2015-12-08","<p>In the academic year 2015 to 2016 there were 5,440 first year undergraduate trainees.</p><br /><p>The 2015 to 2016 Teacher Supply Model sets the target for postgraduate trainees and takes account of the number of undergraduate trainees completing a course in 2016 when meeting future teacher requirements. We allocated places for undergraduate courses using criteria as set out in the published guidance.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb","18682","2015-12-08T17:31:10.397Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433956/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433956/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433956/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-12-03","Teachers: Training","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, for what reasons targets and breakdown of recruitment by subject for undergraduate trainees were not included in the Initial Teacher Training census 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","18685"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433957","Department for Education","false","2015-12-08","<p>The latest statistics on the average salaries of teachers employed by schools and local authorities in England are in Tables 8 and 9 of the ‘School Workforce in England: November 2014’ statistical release which was published in July 2015: <a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/school-workforce-in-england-november-2014" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/school-workforce-in-england-november-2014</a></p><p>The latest available statistics on the average salaries of teaching assistants employed by schools and local authorities in England were published in PQ856 in June 2015 in Hansard at the following link:</p><p><a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2015-06-02/856/" target="_blank">http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2015-06-02/856/</a></p><p>The Department for Education’s pay reforms have given schools greater flexibility to decide how much to pay their teachers and how quickly their pay progresses over time.</p><p>Future average salaries of teachers will be informed by the annual recommendations of the School Teachers Pay Review Body; the pay of teaching assistants and school support staff are set by schools themselves. The department does not produce forecasts of future average pay for these staff.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2015-12-08T17:39:16.633Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433957/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433957/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433957/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-12-03","Teachers and Classroom Assistants: Per Capita Costs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what her most recent estimate is of the average annual cost to a (a) school and (b) local authority of employing a (i) teacher and (ii) classroom assistant; and what forecast she has made of the likely equivalent cost in each year from 2015-16 to 2019-20.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","18686"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433958","Department for Education","false","2015-12-09","<p>Collective worship plays an important role in schools. It encourages children to reflect on belief, and helps shape fundamental British values of tolerance, respect and understanding for others. Parents can choose to withdraw their children from all or any part of collective worship.</p><br /><p>The Department does not issue guidance to schools specifically on the provision of meetings for prayer or religious instruction for pupils during break times.</p><br /><p>The Department does publish guidance on collective worship; it is for governing bodies to decide how best to meet the requirements of that guidance and the relevant legislation, which can be found online at GOV.UK:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/281929/Collective_worship_in_schools.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/281929/Collective_worship_in_schools.pdf</a></p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2015-12-09T13:48:49.187Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433958/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433958/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433958/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-12-03","Schools: Religion","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what guidance her Department has issued to schools on meetings for prayer or religious instruction for pupils during break times.","false","Biography information for Sir Mark Hendrick","Preston","Mr Mark Hendrick","18688"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433959","Department for Education","false","2015-12-09","<p>In the academic year 2014/15, 33 academies were opened in rural locations, whose predecessor schools had been deemed ‘inadequate’ in Ofsted inspections prior to conversion.</p>","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2015-12-09T13:35:15.92Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433959/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433959/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433959/answer","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433959/answer/previousversion/34466","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433959/answer/previousversion/34466",,,"60","Education","Education","2015-12-03","Academies: Rural Areas","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, how many schools in rural areas rated by Ofsted as inadequate became academies in 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","18643"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433960","Department for Education","false","2015-12-14","<p>All children’s centres must provide access to health services – either by providing the services or by providing advice and assistance on gaining access to services. Local authorities and local health commissioners have statutory duties to consider providing services through children’s centres to ensure that families get access to the services they need. The transfer of responsibility for public health services to local authorities in October this year provides new opportunities for local areas to configure health services to best effect.</p><br /><p>The Department of Health has been working with local authorities in order to ensure sharing regular and timely updates of live birth data between NHS trusts and children’s centres and have mapped out a process for putting in place appropriate arrangements to support a national solution.</p><br /><p>Children's centres can also have a key role in delivering integrated reviews, which check a child's health and educational progress at age two.</p><br /><p>Future policy on the role of children's centres in supporting expectant parents and improving integrated working among antenatal support services will be informed by the planned consultation on the future of children’s centre services, which is due to be launched shortly. The consultation will offer parents, prospective parents, carers, local authorities and key stakeholders the opportunity to influence and drive what we expect from children’s centre services and where we see them having the greatest impact.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2015-12-14T12:51:35.567Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433960/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433960/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433960/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-12-03","Children's Centres: Antenatal Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, if she will take steps to increase the role of children's centres in supporting expectant parents and improving integrated working among antenatal support services.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","18617"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433961","Department for Business, Innovation and Skills","false","2016-04-22","<p>I refer the hon. Member to the answer I gave to PQ UIN <a href="http://www.parliament.uk/business/publications/written-questions-answers-statements/written-question/Commons/2015-12-03/18668/" target="_blank">18668</a>.</p>","Orpington","Joseph Johnson",,"2016-04-22T09:25:19.363Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433961/answer","Biography information for Joseph  Johnson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433961/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433961/answer",,,,,,,,"26","Business, Innovation and Skills","Business, Innovation and Skills","2015-12-03","Students: Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Innovation and Skills, what his Department's timetable is for the implementation of the provision of postgraduate student loans of up to £10,000.","false","Biography information for Julie Cooper","Burnley","Julie Cooper","18610"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433962","Department for Education","false","2015-12-08","<p>The data provided to the Department for Education by schools in the School Workforce Census, November 2014, shows that 72 per cent of classroom teachers earning £65,000 or more were women.</p>","Bognor Regis and Littlehampton","Nick Gibb",,"2015-12-08T17:29:33.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433962/answer","Biography information for Nick Gibb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433962/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433962/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-12-03","Teachers: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, what proportion of classroom teachers earning £65,000 or more per year are women.","false","Biography information for Nic Dakin","Scunthorpe","Nic Dakin","18763"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433963","Department for Education","false","2015-12-11","<p>To allow response to PQ 18764, please find attached an Excel workbook detailing:</p><p>- The Free Schools, Studio Schools and University Technical Colleges (UTCs) open as at 1<sup>st</sup> September 2014;</p><p>- Their funded pupil numbers for the academic year 2014 to 2015;</p><p>- Their recorded pupil numbers as per the October 2014 school census.</p><br />","Crewe and Nantwich","Edward Timpson",,"2015-12-11T13:27:48.947Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433963/answer","Biography information for Edward Timpson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433963/answer","PQ18764_pupil_numbers_2014.xls","PQ18764_pupil_numbers_2014.xls","PQ18764 pupil numbers 2014","PQ18764 pupil numbers 2014","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433963/answer",,,,,,,,"60","Education","Education","2015-12-03","Free Schools","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Education, pursuant to the Answer of 6 January 2014 to Question 17343, what free schools her Department funded for 2014-15; how many children were enrolled at each such school in the autumn term 2014; and for how many children each such school received funding for the academic year 2014-15.","false","Biography information for Jess Phillips","Birmingham, Yardley","Jess Phillips","18764"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433964","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-12-10","<p>The CCS Competition opened in April 2012, with bids invited by July 2012. Eight bids were submitted: North East Oxyfuel Project, Peterhead CCS, Teesside Low Carbon, White Rose (Capture Power), Captain Clean Energy Limited, Don Valley CCS, National Grid Humber Cluster and National Grid Teesside Cluster. Four full chain projects were shortlisted in October 2012. On 14 January 2013, shortlisted bidders submitted revised proposals and later that year the Government announced two preferred bidders, Capture Power Ltd’ White Rose Project and Shell’s Peterhead Project, who were later awarded contracts to undertake Front End Engineering and Design (FEED) studies. Captain Clean Energy and Teesside Low Carbon, the remaining two shortlisted bidders, were appointed as reserve projects until such time as FEED contracts were signed.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-12-10T12:24:51.017Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433964/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433964/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433964/answer","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433964/answer/previousversion/34432","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433964/answer/previousversion/34432",,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-12-03","Carbon Capture and Storage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what bids her Department received for the carbon capture and storage technology completion which the Government is no longer funding.","false","Biography information for Angus Brendan MacNeil","Na h-Eileanan an Iar","Angus Brendan MacNeil","18629"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433965","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-12-14","<p>In 2009 the Don Valley Project was awarded a €180m European Energy Programme for Recovery grant which contributes towards the feasibility and design phase of the project's development. The award is still in place and ~€125m has so far been claimed. In 2013 the White Rose CCS project was awarded up to €300m in potential NER300 funding. This award, which remains available, is subject to the project being able to successfully store carbon dioxide before the end of June 2020.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-12-14T14:52:12.79Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433965/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433965/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433965/answer","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433965/answer/previousversion/34433","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433965/answer/previousversion/34433",,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-12-03","Carbon Capture and Storage: EU Grants and Loans","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, how much EU funding was allocated to the operation of carbon capture and storage projects which is not now available for spending on UK projects.","false","Biography information for Angus Brendan MacNeil","Na h-Eileanan an Iar","Angus Brendan MacNeil","18630"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433966","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-12-14","<p>The provision of ring-fenced capital support for CCS was judged against other Government funding priorities as part of the Spending Review. My department has paid £78.6m between 2011/12 and November 2015 on the CCS Competition including the investment in Front End Engineering and Design (approximately £60 million), independent professional technical, legal, financial and commercial advice and civil service staff.</p><br /><p>The Government continues to view CCS as having a potential role in the long-term decarbonisation of the UK’s power and industrial sectors, and considers that the investment to date remains value for money to the UK.</p><p><br></p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-12-14T14:54:41.82Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433966/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433966/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433966/answer","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433966/answer/previousversion/34435","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433966/answer/previousversion/34435",,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-12-03","Carbon Capture and Storage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what assessment she made of the value for money of carbon capture and storage before the Government's carbon capture and storage competition was suspended; and how much from the public purse had been spent on that competition at the time of suspension.","false","Biography information for Angus Brendan MacNeil","Na h-Eileanan an Iar","Angus Brendan MacNeil","18631"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433967","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-12-10","<p>The provision of ring-fenced capital support for CCS was judged against other Government funding priorities as part of the Spending Review. We are currently engaging with both bidders regarding the implications of this decision on their Bids.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-12-10T13:13:20.477Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433967/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433967/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433967/answer","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433967/answer/previousversion/34436","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433967/answer/previousversion/34436",,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-12-03","Carbon Capture and Storage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what assessment her Department made of the value for money of the carbon capture and storage project bids.","false","Biography information for Callum McCaig","Aberdeen South","Callum McCaig","18632"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433968","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-12-10","<p>Through the CCS Competition the Department has held discussions on a regular basis with both Shell and Capture Power Ltd. We continue to engage closely with the two bidders on the implications of the Spending Review decision for their Bids.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-12-10T13:30:18.987Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433968/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433968/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433968/answer","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433968/answer/previousversion/34437","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433968/answer/previousversion/34437",,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-12-03","Carbon Capture and Storage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what discussions she had with bidders for the carbon capture and storage competition prior to the decision to withdraw funding earmarked for that competition.","false","Biography information for Callum McCaig","Aberdeen South","Callum McCaig","18633"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433969","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-12-10","<p>The Government continues to view CCS as having a potential role in the long-term decarbonisation of the UK’s power and industrial sectors.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-12-10T13:34:45.997Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433969/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433969/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433969/answer","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433969/answer/previousversion/34439","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433969/answer/previousversion/34439",,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-12-03","Carbon Capture and Storage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what the Government's future plans are for carbon capture and storage.","false","Biography information for Callum McCaig","Aberdeen South","Callum McCaig","18634"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433970","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-12-10","<p>The provision of ring-fenced capital support for CCS was judged against other Government funding priorities as part of the Spending Review. We are engaging closely with the two bidders and wider industry on the implications of the decision. The Government’s view remains that CCS has a potential role in the long term decarbonisation of the UK’s power and industrial sectors.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-12-10T13:35:14.507Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433970/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433970/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433970/answer","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433970/answer/previousversion/34440","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433970/answer/previousversion/34440",,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-12-03","Carbon Capture and Storage","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, what assessment she has made of the potential effect on (a) the supply chain and (b) existing infrastructure of the Government's decision to cancel the carbon capture and storage competition.","false","Biography information for Callum McCaig","Aberdeen South","Callum McCaig","18635"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433971","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-12-15","<p>We are currently analysing feedback submitted during the Feed-in Tariff review consultation and intend to publish a Government response as soon as possible.</p><br />","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-12-15T15:20:40.127Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433971/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433971/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433971/answer",,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-12-03","Renewable Energy: Feed-in Tariffs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, when she plans to publish her Department's response to the consultation on a review of the feed-in tariff scheme.","false","Biography information for Huw Irranca-Davies","Ogmore","Huw Irranca-Davies","18672"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433972","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-12-09","<p>Officials have begun discussions with stakeholders, and we plan to consult on the changes in the New Year.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-12-09T17:08:02.49Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433972/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433972/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433972/answer",,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-12-03","Renewable Heat Incentive Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, when she plans to publish details of how her Department plans to reform the Renewable Heat Incentive scheme to make the savings announced in the Autumn Statement 2015.","false","Biography information for Huw Irranca-Davies","Ogmore","Huw Irranca-Davies","18670"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433973","Department for Energy and Climate Change","false","2015-12-09","<p>We are still at an early stage in the process of reforming the Renewable Heat Incentive (RHI). Therefore, I am unable to make specific commitments as to the future shape of the scheme at this point.</p><br /><p>However, Ofgem will continue to run the RHI under the current rules, while we consider reform of the scheme.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2015-12-09T17:09:10.153Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433973/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433973/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433973/answer",,,,,,,,"63","Energy and Climate Change","Energy and Climate Change","2015-12-03","Renewable Heat Incentive Scheme","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Energy and Climate Change, whether it is her policy that anaerobic digestion will continue to be supported under the reformed Renewable Heat Incentive scheme.","false","Biography information for Huw Irranca-Davies","Ogmore","Huw Irranca-Davies","18671"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433974","Department for Communities and Local Government","false","2015-12-08","<p>The outcome of the review of how the planning system in England can support the delivery of mobile connectivity will be announced in due course.</p><br />","Great Yarmouth","Brandon Lewis",,"2015-12-08T15:21:04.503Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433974/answer","Biography information for Brandon Lewis","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433974/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433974/answer",,,,,,,,"7","Communities and Local Government","Communities and Local Government","2015-12-03","Aerials: Planning Permission","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Communities and Local Government, when he plans to publish the outcome of his call for evidence on extending permitted development rights to taller mobile telephone masts.","false","Biography information for Seema Malhotra","Feltham and Heston","Seema Malhotra","18661"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433975","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-12-09","<p>I discussed the issue of colistin resistance on 1 December with the Chief Executive of the Veterinary Medicines Directorate following the publication of a report on the issue in relation to China.</p><br /><p>In November, the UK Government attended an EU workshop on the impact on public health and animal health of the use of antibiotics in animals, which included the use of colistin. The Veterinary Medicines Directorate has also held initial discussions on the use of colistin and colistin resistance with other experts across government, including the Food Standards Agency, Department of Health and Public Health England, and key industry bodies.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2015-12-09T10:44:36.033Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433975/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433975/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433975/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-12-03","Antibiotics","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what recent discussions she has had with veterinary experts on the use of colistin and colistin resistance in animals, food and humans.","false","Biography information for Crispin Blunt","Reigate","Crispin Blunt","18673"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433976","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-12-11","<br /><p>The Secretary of State and I have regular meetings and discussions with the Chief Executive of the Rural Payments Agency (RPA). The Chief Executive of the RPA also attends the department’s weekly Executive Committee.</p><br /><p>Around 33,000 Basic Payment Scheme claims were paid promptly and accurately on 1st December, the first day of the payment window that runs through to 30 June.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","18712","2015-12-11T13:57:28.027Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433976/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433976/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433976/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-12-03","Rural Payments Agency","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what recent steps she has taken to improve the administration of the Rural Payments Agency.","false","Biography information for Bill Wiggin","North Herefordshire","Bill Wiggin","18711"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433977","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2015-12-11","<br /><p>The Secretary of State and I have regular meetings and discussions with the Chief Executive of the Rural Payments Agency (RPA). The Chief Executive of the RPA also attends the department’s weekly Executive Committee.</p><br /><p>Around 33,000 Basic Payment Scheme claims were paid promptly and accurately on 1st December, the first day of the payment window that runs through to 30 June.</p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice","18711","2015-12-11T13:57:28.087Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433977/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433977/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/433977/answer",,,,,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2015-12-03","Agriculture: Subsidies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, how many single farm payments were issued by the Rural Payments Agency on 1 December 2015; and how many of those payments were calculated incorrectly.","true","Biography information for Bill Wiggin","North Herefordshire","Bill Wiggin","18712"
